args: Yooooo, I took some FIRE snapshots today!
Oho ho, this selfie is EVERYTHING.\nWhat a total serve.
What's this behind me in the shot...?!
To unravel the terrifying truth behind the phantom\n＂something＂ in her selfie, Nadine convenes a\nmeeting of intellectual experts.
...and that's why I need all of you Halidom\nsmarties to put your galaxy brains together\nand help a girl out!
Heh. A most fascinating mystery indeed.\nIt would be my singular pleasure to assist.
I must agree! This is a sterling opportunity\nto probe into an unknown creature's origin.\nWheee hee ha ha ho!
Heh heh heh... In all honesty, I am most\ncurious about that magical device itself.
It can record a moment in time! What sort\nof mechanism does it employ? Oh, how I\nyearn to dismantle it for its secrets!
Hey, if you wanna know how it works,\nI'll just tell you, dude. Clix here uses\nmaterium to take light mana and—
Wait, both of you.\nWe're getting off-topic.
Yeah! We were talking about whatever\nmystery thing showed up in that photo\nyou took, weren't we?
Yeah, that's right. Thanks, Bro-Hein!\nAnd you too, Mymz!
But wait. What're you even doing here,\nMymz? I don't remember hitting you up.
I'm here because I have a clue about what\nthat thing in the picture could be, silly!
For reals?! Girl, spill the tea!
So get this: on Halloween, I ran across\nthis mystery thing that wasn't a person,\nwasn't a fiend, and wasn't a dragon, either.
It appeared outta nowhere and was like,\n＂BOO!＂ Almost gave me a heart attack.\nNext thing I knew, ZOOP—it was gone!
Oho! And the figure in the photo does\nseem indistinct, like it's about to\ndisappear. Quite similar indeed!
Right?! It must've shown up again\nto scare the heck out of Nadine!
Estelle said she saw something weird on\nHalloween, too. There must be some kinda\nmischief maker skulking around the castle.
You would posit that we contend with\nsome manner of incorporeal phantom?\nWhee ha hoo hah! EXCITEMENT!

I daresay it could be a wandering soul.
If we can nail down the conditions for this
phenomenon to occur, I could make great
strides in my research.
Let the investigation begin!\nGuide us to the site where you\nencountered this being.
Can do. If I remember correctly,\nit was around...
Hey, hold up! I'm coming too!
Look alive, guys, or else Special Klei\nand Mymz are gonna leave us behind!
Before that, a query: when did\nyou take the picture in question?
Last night. I remember 'cause the literal\nSECOND I took the snap, I heard\nCle-o-rama yelling that dinner was ready.
I see. Then let us leave that matter to\nthose two. We will remain here.
Why, you ask? Because whatever Mym\nencountered and the presence in your\nphoto are two distinct phenomena.
Yeaaah, you're gonna need to say that\nin normal people words.
Mym's encounter was on Halloween.\nLikewise for Estelle.
However, you took your photo just last\nnight; ergo, it was NOT Halloween.
Also, in Mym's case, there was an aural\ncomponent that caught her by surprise.\nNot so in your case.
These facts are enough to convince me that\nwe are talking about two different things.

Ohhh, duh! This is exactly why we keep
you around, Bro-Hein. 'Kay, now let's
bring those brainwaves to bear on the
mystery in my picture!
Yes, well... Heh heh heh. I have\nformulated a rough hypothesis there.
...most definitely the result of interference\nwith the magical device! Hand it over and\nlet me disassemble it to make repairs!
Whaaat?! As if! You're just saying that\nso you can take it apart, aren't you?\nNot gonna happen, my guy!
You MUST! YOU SIMPLY MUST LET ME!
Hm. To be sure, there exists at least some\npossibility that the device malfunctioned.\nCome, Nadine. Let us analyze it.
Et tu, Bro-Hein?! Aaagh, somebody help!
You okay, Nadine?!\nI came flapping as fast as I could!
Notte-tay! It's Sha-Zam—\nhe's trying to break Clix!
He's doing WHAT? Shame on you,\nSha Wujing. I'm gonna tell Cleo!
Whew... That was clutch, Notte-tay. Thanx.
Anytime, girl. You wanna fill me in\non what's going down here?
Okay, so this is totally gonna take you to\nspooksville, but hear me out. There's\nsomething weird in this selfie I took. Look.
HOLY CHOCOLATE CANNOLI! You weren't\nkidding. You took this yesterday around\ndinnertime in the courtyard, right?
Because I was there! I heard Cleo sound\nthe dinner bell, so I passed right by you...
But I sure as heck didn't see anything\nfreaky like THIS hanging around!
For reals?! So whatever it is, it\ncan't be seen by the naked eye?\nThat's BONKS spoopy!
...I see. So that's what we're dealing with.
Did you just have an a-tiffany\nor whatever, Bro-Hein?!
An epiphany? Yes. The truth behind\nthis mystery is quite simple, really.\nThe unknown entity in the picture is...
When you say ＂now,＂ you mean, like,\nRIGHT now? Even though it's invisible or\nwhatever? I'm about to lose it here...
You gotta be kidding.\nPlease say psych, Heinwald!

My apologies—it seems I've engendered
a misunderstanding. Allow me to reword
my conclusion. The true identity of the
photographed phantom is...
Oh, duh, of course it's—\nWait, what the flap?! This is me?
Yes. Merely connect the dots and you will\nunderstand. Nadine, when you took this\npicture, you heard Cleo calling, yes?
Meanwhile, Notte heard the same voice\nas she was flitting behind you. It is only\nlogical that you captured her in the photo.
＂But Heinwald,＂ you protest, ＂all I see is a\nblur in the background, not a wise-cracking\nfaerie on her way to gorge upon supper.＂
This is because Notte and the blur are one\nand the same. The answer is that simple.

I see. In other words, it is a sort of
afterimage. Depending on the speed at
which an arrow flies, it sometimes appears
as if there are two or even three.
And Clix, like the eye of a person, cannot\nquite perceive something moving that\nswiftly, and so captures a sort of shadow.
The proof is in the picture, if you ask me.\nTry taking a picture of Notte as she flies.
Whoa, you're right...\nIt's blur city, population Notte-tay!
I am so relieved it isn't even funny.\nSo much for that freaky mystery.

Seriously! I was about to write a strongly
worded letter asking the prince to bolster
patrols so I wouldn't have a panic attack
going to the bathroom at night!
Heh heh... How quickly you forget—\nwhatever Mym and the others saw has\nyet to be identified.
Now, then. Let us join them on their\ninvestigation. I suspect therein lies a\nworthy mystery.
Come along, Nadine. That Clix of yours\nwill prove useful in capturing evidence.
Suddenly I wish I knew more languages\nso I could say ＂no＂ in all of 'em.
My Clix is for fire selfies and good vibes\nONLY, my dude. Turbo no on the spookies!
